Title: 6 Newbie tips, post you 50 spambumps here.
Post by: DocFireTyve on February 10, 2013, 04:27 am
So i dont really like spamming, and have tried keeping my 50 post to useful ones,
but it takes to much time to get there this way, so here goes my spam thread.
At least it is a tad bit more useful than most.

Few important newbie tips:

1.
To become a member, able to post in rest of the forums, you need to get 50 post.
i know its stupid, but its a measure to prevent scammers from spamming the forums.
feel free to use this thread to spam your 50 bumps, so other newbs can read these tips.

2.
watch?v=SywCI91kfq0&feature=youtu.be
watch this on youtube, for your own safety, you need pgp.
it will ensure that if SR is compromised, they wont get your information without your vendor.

3.
use real name and address, but dont have drugs shipped were they are stored.
you might get a controlled delivery, were they stop the package, find the content,
send it through and bust you once you take the package home.
always be sure you can deny any knowledge about the package.

4.research your vendors, not only on rating and feedback, but also on the forums.
you never know who have their account hacked or turns a scammer once the reputation and trust is built.

5. use anonymous ways to get bitcoins, cash/moneypack/anon-visa are good ways to use. for vendors you might visit localbitcoins.com

6. dont finalize early, unless its a trusted vendor. (if you do, you run a high risk of being scammed)
vendors are not allowed to require you to FE unless special conditions.
however high rated, well trusted sellers have always been allowed to.



now i hope this help explain the basics you need to know before using SilkRoad.
Welcome newbies :)

- DFT

big question is -- when I arrange my payment thru bitcopia, do i really need give my "normal" name and email addy or will a fake email addy (signed up for thru tor ((even though not a tormail account- hotmail or whatnot)),   ) for confirmation of the transaction.   or should I just use same user handle (example --- SWR79@silkroad.onion or whatever as my forum account) which ultimately is never checked in the clearnet?

sorry if these seem simple questions, but im attempting a new "route" and am trying to "line up me ducks" before I shoot.  many thanks and much blessings to the road!

Post by: ShadowCrewTheHive on March 06, 2013, 06:12 pm
Quote from: DocFireTyve on February 10, 2013, 04:27 am
So i dont really like spamming, and have tried keeping my 50 post to useful ones,
but it takes to much time to get there this way, so here goes my spam thread.
At least it is a tad bit more useful than most.

Few important newbie tips:

1.
To become a member, able to post in rest of the forums, you need to get 50 post.
i know its stupid, but its a measure to prevent scammers from spamming the forums.
feel free to use this thread to spam your 50 bumps, so other newbs can read these tips.

2.
watch?v=SywCI91kfq0&feature=youtu.be
watch this on youtube, for your own safety, you need pgp.
it will ensure that if SR is compromised, they wont get your information without your vendor.

3.
use real name and address, but dont have drugs shipped were they are stored.
you might get a controlled delivery, were they stop the package, find the content,
send it through and bust you once you take the package home.
always be sure you can deny any knowledge about the package.

4.research your vendors, not only on rating and feedback, but also on the forums.
you never know who have their account hacked or turns a scammer once the reputation and trust is built.

5. use anonymous ways to get bitcoins, cash/moneypack/anon-visa are good ways to use. for vendors you might visit localbitcoins.com

6. dont finalize early, unless its a trusted vendor. (if you do, you run a high risk of being scammed)
vendors are not allowed to require you to FE unless special conditions.
however high rated, well trusted sellers have always been allowed to.



now i hope this help explain the basics you need to know before using SilkRoad.
Welcome newbies :)

- DFT

Morning,

Morning.

Well, there's egg and bacon,
egg sausage and bacon
Egg and spam
Egg, bacon and spam
Egg, bacon, sausage and spam
Spam, bacon, sausage and spam
Spam, egg, spam, spam, bacon and spam
Spam, sausage, spam, spam, spam, bacon, spam tomato and spam
Spam, spam, spam, egg and spam
Spam, spam, spam, spam, spam, spam, baked beans, spam, spam, spam and spam.

(Choir: Spam! Spam! Spam! Spam! Lovely Spam! Lovely Spam!)

Or Lobster Thermidor aux crevettes with a mornay sauce
served in a provencale manner with shallots and aubergines
garnished with truffle pate, brandy and a fried egg on top and spam.

Have you got anything without spam?

Well, the spam, eggs, sausage and spam
That's not got much spam in it

I don't want any spam!

Customer:
Why can't she have eggs, bacon, spam and sausage?

That's got spam in it!

Customer:
Hasn't got much spam in it as spam, eggs, sausage and spam has it?

(Choir: Spam! Spam! Spam!...)

Iiiiiiiiiiiich!!

Shut up!

Shut Up! Bloody Vikings!

spam and spam?

Title: Re: 6 Newbie tips, post you 50 spambumps here.
Post by: seeyallnextyear on March 13, 2013, 11:51 pm
Tip #1  Do your research and always read the vendor's ENTIRE profile page before ordering.
Tip #2  Keep up with your PIN. And NEVER ever give it out to anyone. It is only used for purchasing and withdrawals.
Tip #3  Do your best to stay in escrow and keep your buyer stats clean and trustworthy.
Tip #4  Never FE unless it is absolutely necessary. Only if you are in absolute desperation after scouring the entire road to no avail.  Or if you are a first time buyer or have less than impressive buyer stats.
Tip #5  Always encrypt using PGP.  If you are unsure how to do this..... Learn!! Tor is anonymous yes, but not everyone understands how to use Tor correctly. Tor makes it damn hard for LE to track you, but even a blind piggy finds the mud every once in a while.
Tip #6  Last but not least, utilize this forum. Every question you have about anything that has to with anything SR is in this forum. Common sense goes a long way.

Bonus Tip ~ Watch out for scammers and spammers. Don't scam and spam.  And Never Ever Scam Me!!!

Thank you for your time.

Title: Re: 6 Newbie tips, post you 50 spambumps here.
Post by: alwayssmoken12345 on March 29, 2013, 04:57 pm
Quote from: DocFireTyve on February 10, 2013, 04:27 am
So i dont really like spamming, and have tried keeping my 50 post to useful ones,
but it takes to much time to get there this way, so here goes my spam thread.
At least it is a tad bit more useful than most.

Few important newbie tips:

1.
To become a member, able to post in rest of the forums, you need to get 50 post.
i know its stupid, but its a measure to prevent scammers from spamming the forums.
feel free to use this thread to spam your 50 bumps, so other newbs can read these tips.

2.
watch?v=SywCI91kfq0&feature=youtu.be
watch this on youtube, for your own safety, you need pgp.
it will ensure that if SR is compromised, they wont get your information without your vendor.

3.
use real name and address, but dont have drugs shipped were they are stored.
you might get a controlled delivery, were they stop the package, find the content,
send it through and bust you once you take the package home.
always be sure you can deny any knowledge about the package.

4.research your vendors, not only on rating and feedback, but also on the forums.
you never know who have their account hacked or turns a scammer once the reputation and trust is built.

5. use anonymous ways to get bitcoins, cash/moneypack/anon-visa are good ways to use. for vendors you might visit localbitcoins.com

6. dont finalize early, unless its a trusted vendor. (if you do, you run a high risk of being scammed)
vendors are not allowed to require you to FE unless special conditions.
however high rated, well trusted sellers have always been allowed to.



now i hope this help explain the basics you need to know before using SilkRoad.
Welcome newbies :)

- DFT

you might get a controlled delivery, were they stop the package, find the content,
send it through and bust you once you take the package home.
always be sure you can deny any knowledge about the package.

4.research your vendors, not only on rating and feedback, but also on the forums.
you never know who have their account hacked or turns a scammer once the reputation and trust is built.

5. use anonymous ways to get bitcoins, cash/moneypack/anon-visa are good ways to use. for vendors you might visit localbitcoins.com

6. dont finalize early, unless its a trusted vendor. (if you do, you run a high risk of being scammed)
vendors are not allowed to require you to FE unless special conditions.
however high rated, well trusted sellers have always been allowed to.



now i hope this help explain the basics you need to know before using SilkRoad.
Welcome newbies :)

- DFT

Thanks for the infomation

Post by: pluto411 on March 29, 2013, 06:00 pm
Here's a tip ...

It took two business days to get my bit coins once I ordered them.

Also, it took an hour to deposit them in SR once I made my first order.  The price went up .02 bitcoins in this hour, which meant I had to make another deposit.  It's not worth trying to be exact.

"Yeah teach?" he replies.

"If there are three ducks on a fence and you shoot one of them with a shotgun, how many are left?" asks the teacher.

"Well, teach, I've got a question for you... There are 3 women that come out of an ice-cream parlor, one is biting her ice-cream cone, one is licking it, and one is sucking on it. Which one is married?"

Matt replies "No teach, the one that has the wedding ring on her finger, but I like the way you're thinking!"

Title: Re: 6 Newbie tips, post you 50 spambumps here.
Post by: samaxe1981 on May 05, 2013, 12:57 am
Quote from: DocFireTyve on February 10, 2013, 04:27 am
So i dont really like spamming, and have tried keeping my 50 post to useful ones,
but it takes to much time to get there this way, so here goes my spam thread.
At least it is a tad bit more useful than most.

Few important newbie tips:

1.
To become a member, able to post in rest of the forums, you need to get 50 post.
i know its stupid, but its a measure to prevent scammers from spamming the forums.
feel free to use this thread to spam your 50 bumps, so other newbs can read these tips.

2.
watch?v=SywCI91kfq0&feature=youtu.be
watch this on youtube, for your own safety, you need pgp.
it will ensure that if SR is compromised, they wont get your information without your vendor.

3.
use real name and address, but dont have drugs shipped were they are stored.
you might get a controlled delivery, were they stop the package, find the content,
send it through and bust you once you take the package home.
always be sure you can deny any knowledge about the package.

4.research your vendors, not only on rating and feedback, but also on the forums.
you never know who have their account hacked or turns a scammer once the reputation and trust is built.

5. use anonymous ways to get bitcoins, cash/moneypack/anon-visa are good ways to use. for vendors you might visit localbitcoins.com

6. dont finalize early, unless its a trusted vendor. (if you do, you run a high risk of being scammed)
vendors are not allowed to require you to FE unless special conditions.
however high rated, well trusted sellers have always been allowed to.



now i hope this help explain the basics you need to know before using SilkRoad.
Welcome newbies :)

- DFT

Thanks, Good info.

Title: Re: 6 Newbie tips, post you 50 spambumps here.
Post by: samaxe1981 on June 07, 2013, 03:22 am
Quote from: DocFireTyve on February 10, 2013, 04:27 am
So i dont really like spamming, and have tried keeping my 50 post to useful ones,
but it takes to much time to get there this way, so here goes my spam thread.
At least it is a tad bit more useful than most.

Few important newbie tips:

1.
To become a member, able to post in rest of the forums, you need to get 50 post.
i know its stupid, but its a measure to prevent scammers from spamming the forums.
feel free to use this thread to spam your 50 bumps, so other newbs can read these tips.

2.
watch?v=SywCI91kfq0&feature=youtu.be
watch this on youtube, for your own safety, you need pgp.
it will ensure that if SR is compromised, they wont get your information without your vendor.

3.
use real name and address, but dont have drugs shipped were they are stored.
you might get a controlled delivery, were they stop the package, find the content,
send it through and bust you once you take the package home.
always be sure you can deny any knowledge about the package.

4.research your vendors, not only on rating and feedback, but also on the forums.
you never know who have their account hacked or turns a scammer once the reputation and trust is built.

5. use anonymous ways to get bitcoins, cash/moneypack/anon-visa are good ways to use. for vendors you might visit localbitcoins.com

6. dont finalize early, unless its a trusted vendor. (if you do, you run a high risk of being scammed)
vendors are not allowed to require you to FE unless special conditions.
however high rated, well trusted sellers have always been allowed to.



now i hope this help explain the basics you need to know before using SilkRoad.
Welcome newbies :)

- DFT

watch?v=SywCI91kfq0&feature=youtu.be
watch this on youtube, for your own safety, you need pgp.
it will ensure that if SR is compromised, they wont get your information without your vendor.

3.
use real name and address, but dont have drugs shipped were they are stored.
you might get a controlled delivery, were they stop the package, find the content,
send it through and bust you once you take the package home.
always be sure you can deny any knowledge about the package.

4.research your vendors, not only on rating and feedback, but also on the forums.
you never know who have their account hacked or turns a scammer once the reputation and trust is built.

5. use anonymous ways to get bitcoins, cash/moneypack/anon-visa are good ways to use. for vendors you might visit localbitcoins.com

6. dont finalize early, unless its a trusted vendor. (if you do, you run a high risk of being scammed)
vendors are not allowed to require you to FE unless special conditions.
however high rated, well trusted sellers have always been allowed to.



now i hope this help explain the basics you need to know before using SilkRoad.
Welcome newbies :)

- DFT

Title: Re: 6 Newbie tips, post you 50 spambumps here.
Post by: Pot Doctor Vendor on August 11, 2013, 03:45 pm
Quote from: DocFireTyve on February 10, 2013, 04:27 am
So i dont really like spamming, and have tried keeping my 50 post to useful ones,
but it takes to much time to get there this way, so here goes my spam thread.
At least it is a tad bit more useful than most.

Few important newbie tips:

1.
To become a member, able to post in rest of the forums, you need to get 50 post.
i know its stupid, but its a measure to prevent scammers from spamming the forums.
feel free to use this thread to spam your 50 bumps, so other newbs can read these tips.

2.
watch?v=SywCI91kfq0&feature=youtu.be
watch this on youtube, for your own safety, you need pgp.
it will ensure that if SR is compromised, they wont get your information without your vendor.

3.
use real name and address, but dont have drugs shipped were they are stored.
you might get a controlled delivery, were they stop the package, find the content,
send it through and bust you once you take the package home.
always be sure you can deny any knowledge about the package.

4.research your vendors, not only on rating and feedback, but also on the forums.
you never know who have their account hacked or turns a scammer once the reputation and trust is built.

5. use anonymous ways to get bitcoins, cash/moneypack/anon-visa are good ways to use. for vendors you might visit localbitcoins.com

6. dont finalize early, unless its a trusted vendor. (if you do, you run a high risk of being scammed)
vendors are not allowed to require you to FE unless special conditions.
however high rated, well trusted sellers have always been allowed to.



now i hope this help explain the basics you need to know before using SilkRoad.
Welcome newbies :)

- DFT
